<div><h4>5 Cs in Credit-One more step guide to get your loan sanctioned</h4>
 <p>The banks generally follow Converserative approach of processing the loan request of the borrowers.In this analysis bankers consider five elements and these are known as 5Cs of credits.they are:<br></p>
<p><b>Capital:</b>Capital is the money you personally have invested in the business and is an individual of how much you have at risk should the buisness fail.</p>
<p><b>Collatral:</b>Bank insists on security that is created out of loan proceeds.Conditions described the intended purpose of the loan.Will the money be used for working capital additional equipment or inventory?</p>
<p><b>Capacity:</b>The prospective lender will want to know exactly how you intend and your capital to repay the loan.</p>
<p><b>Character:</b>The lender will form a subjective opinion as to whether or not you are sufficiently trustworthy to repay the loan or generate a return on funds invested in your company</p>
	<h3>Credit Score</h3>
<p> Credit Information agency spare a vital role in decision making in loan-application process.After an applicant fills out the application form and hence it over to the lender, The lender first check the credit score and credit report of the applicant.
If the credit score is low the lender may not even consider the application further & Reject it at that point.If the credit score is high, The lender will look into the application and consider other details to determine if the applicant is credit worthy.
The credit scores  works as a first impression for the lender, the higher the score, the better your chances of loan being reviewed and approved.The decision to lend a loan is solely dependent on the lender and the credit score for credit report does not In any manner decide if the loan or credit card should be sanctioned or not. </p>
<p>Credit information bureau (India) Ltd (CIBIL) is India's first credit information company,Also commonly referred as credit bureau.CIBIL Collects and maintains record of individuals and non individuals (commercial entities) payments repairing loans and credit cards.
These records are submitted to CIBIL by banks and other lenders on monthly basis; Using this information a credit information report (CIR)and credit score is developed in a believer lenders to evaluate an approved loan application. Credit Bureau is licensed by the RBI and governed by the credit information companies(Regulations) Act of 2005.
 The Reserve Bank of India acquires all credit bureaus to give a full credit report every year to all the consumers</p>
